SCREENDOOR

Available at:  http://github.com/write2david/screendoor



USE
Begin using screendoor.sh by adding a line like this to the end of a file like .bash_login and .bashrc

. [path to screendoor]/screendoor.sh



EXAMPLE
. ~/screendoor.sh




TIPS

May be good to put something like this in your .screenrc

defscrollback 10000
# Window tabs, second to last line
# caption always "%{kW}%?%-Lw%?%{bw}%n*%f %t%?(%u)%?%{kW}%?%+Lw%? %= %{= Wk}%110`%109`%122`%111`"
caption always "%{= .w}%-Lw%20L>%{=b .c}%n%f %t%{-}%+Lw %-020= %D %d %M - %c"